column5: Last day at Jiggy, home tomorrow but back REALLY soon!!	heres some pictures from today, used the Mangler frog lures I got... nailed some pike will trolling and kicked ass for bass off the dock!!  Great day, great dinner, great sunset....                             Till next time ..... booooo hooooo......
Great looking fish TJ.Interesting lure too. Never seen one of those.
So when I get there tomorrow I'm only gonna find empty beer cans again and no bounding beauty greeting me dock side....  Glad you two's had a great time away!
Some nice fish and some awesome photography there TJ. One question though. Why is that duck mooning you??
Excellent, TJ! You'll be back up there in no time. I can feel it.
Nice work! Now I want one of those lures.
Awesome! You guys have so much fun
This man knows how to live!
Looking good TJ.  Love Monique's nails  Oh ya, nice fish too
Wow, you've really made that place comfy looking.  Interesting lure, does it double as a bottle opener?
Nice size bass man!  Is Jiggy part of the OFC Community?

Thanks all!!! Im hoping to get up here as much as possible in august.	The Lures are the Mangler frog lures, you can use em as a topwater and then they dive down about a foot for the retrieve, the side to side action is really good. I casted and trolled all day with them.    I have ni idea why the duck is mooning me, and wayne, stay tuned , youll have lots of time to visit!!  Joey, i think its her nails that attract the fish!!!
nice fish buddy thanks for the link it looks like a lure different enough for the fish to not know what it is yet.   Art
Okay TJ... let me know what day you'll be off to town for beer and Monique will be there to catch me at the dock !!
Paradise!!! This month especially!!August is my fave month up north, the bugs are dying off and it's not as smokin' hot as July. Enjoy Bud!!
Looks like a great spot - thanks for sharing !

I ordered some lures from that site on Aug 8th, and they arrived today. Looking forward to trying them out! Great prices, really. Thanks T.J.!  Edit: I tried them out tonight. FIRST CAST I got a smallmouth with the darker green frog! Lost it at the dock as I bent down to grab it the hook popped out, so I didn't get a pic. Great lure!
